ge/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uealadanazurefire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ealadan Azurefire</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/19/02 10:30:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=279.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ideas for quadding in NON dr00d infested areas?</span><hr size=1> Have you tried the succulents and cockatrice in the Overthere?  I was in my low 40s when I first began quad kiting there, but suppose it can be done at 39.  It's worth a try anyway.  Just beware of the Dragoons and the Sarnaks (sometimes they have sow).<br><br>The rhinos and sabretooths run as fast as jboots too I believe. <p><br>Ealadan Azurefire<br>58 Evoker<br>Last Hope of E'ci</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uchifiir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chifiir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/21/02 5:31:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=279.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Quadding OT</span><hr size=1> Best things to quad in OT are Sarnaks, hands down no questions asked.<br><br>Zerkers you can quad at 39.  Start quadding Knights are 40-41.  If you have great gear, you can do them earlier but they like to resist BoFs occasionally.  41 seemed like the &quot;magical&quot; level for Sarnaks in OT.<br><br>Why Sarnaks?<br>They don't flee if they have another one near then.  Birds/Cacti will stop/flee/peel off if they're low on health.  Rhinos and cats are just too fast.<br><br>Things to watch for:<br>The Sarnak ruins hold casters.  Even Sarnaks not IN the ruins may pass by and pick up a SoW/haste.  <br><br>Cats/birds/rhinos will sometimes agro..try to give them a wide berth.<br><br>The best 2 places to quad, IMHO, are either along the South(FM) wall between FM and the East(WW) wall.  <br><br>The other place is along the West(SF) side of chasm.  Not a lot of &quot;creature traffic&quot; along the chasm area, nice and wide open with a large area to pull from.  The ONLY problem I ever had here, one time only, was that I did a tri-kite and somehow shot a scorp guardian down below.<br>Insta-Loading.  Was a fluke, though, and it never happened again, even while trying.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I did 38-44 in OT.  Keep the braids and turn in for xp/faction in the outpost as well, if you can get in.  <br>I was pulling between 1-2 blues at all times per quad.<br>Zerkers are MUCH easier than knights, but less xp.  However, the braid quest helps a LOT.<br><br>At 44, 4 dark blue zerkers + 4 braids ~= 4 knights.<br><br>Zerkers start going light blue around 43-44, so ease of hunting starts dropping.  Move to Specs after OT.<br><br>-Szii Uln'hyrr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chiriko>chiriko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/23/02 10:56:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=279.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding OT</span><hr size=1> I'd say go dwarf's. note: dwarfs are differnt than dwarf guards. if you pick your targets well, you won't lose dwarf guard faction, and you'll still be able to rn through the zone uninvis. But lets face it: when the heck as a wizard are you ever going to go to butcherblock? sure, there's that one epic NPC, but just kill Den standing next to him (Den &amp; friends is my favorite place to quad) and you're fine. best xp around and damn good money too. other than that, yeti's in DL might be doable at 39/40, and dire wolves in GD should be blue/light blue. always lots of those up. kodiaks in GD are doable at 39, but lots of druids camp those..<br><br>-Chiriko, lvl 47 wizard, Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=279.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=279.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=279.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=279.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.threadControl?topicID=279.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=279.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href